metadata.name: (kinder)Garden, Monuments #96
metadata.description:
When Yazid and Zancan started their fxcollab journey, they knew very little about each other. They learnt about their rich cultural differences, their complementary graphic styles, and a 7-hour timezone difference. What they did have in common was each had two kids about the same age (one a pair of girls, the other boys).

Every kid was born a builder; every kid likes to sit in nature. It’s their way of discovering the world and dreaming of their future accomplishments. While they marvel at the heights of the cities and monuments they construct out of stacks of cubes, parents marvel at their ability to elaborate an unlimited range of worlds out of a limited range of materials. 

This project celebrates the humble and versatile cube. A deceptively simple yet powerful object of play and learning, regardless of age, whether you’re stacking them up in a sandbox, or learning 3D graphics for the first time. 

This project is dedicated to kids, those who were once children, to the dreamers and builders who still enjoy playing with cubes.

Coded in Vanilla JS, the project combines Yazid's iconic “Hashed/Hatched” aesthetic incorporated into childhood wooden toy block structures, and Zancan's signature lush foliage and framework, which enables all iterations to be plottable.
 
Controls (in live view):
- Press [s] to get a SVG file suited for plotters
- Click on the image to download a 4K resolution PNG

metadata.name: Intricate 4x4 #3
metadata.description:
'Intricated 4x4' was one of the projects that took me the longest to develop. With each WIP, I realized that I could improve some detail, some feature looking for more pleasant, democratic and varied aesthetic results.

This work consists of generating four sets of particles (ellipses or squares) that appear in the four corners of the screen, respecting the predefined margin limits. These sets move towards the center following an attenuated decrease in size thanks to the combination of logarithm and mapping of frameCount and the size variable. This simple trick ensures smoother and less aggressive movements, bringing the observer a sense of tranquility. 

Combining the use of different palettes with some movement conditionals - functions back() and go() - and a charming touch of shading and depth, 'Intricated 4x4' can be considered one of my favorite 
works and I hope it will be for you, after the mint.

Palletes carefully chosen =)

_______________________________
Variability of editions is ensured by:
* 8 background colors
* 13 palettes x 4 colors = 52 colors picked one by one with a lot of care
* possibility to have a fantastic BW version (rarity: 5%)
* possibility to repeat the same palette for both sets (rarity: 8%)
* possibility to have squares intead of circles (rarity: 25%)
* a wide range of Shapes number
* a well thought number of frames, proportional to the total frameCount to make things 'softer'

_______________________________
Interactive instructions:
* Press [S] to save your .png file
* Press [P] to play/pause your animation anytime you like (this increase exponentially your possibilities, right!?)

_______________________________
Creator: Kukuti
May 2022
License: NFT 2.0

metadata.name: Celestial Collisions  #195
metadata.description:
Celestial Collisions  - The following series is an exploration of organic textures that embodies the way of a gentle breeze and the simulation of color pencils that randomly generates simple shapes. Out of 380K different combinations of the following combinations,
an endless amount of orientations can be produced from the piece of work.  

For the interactivity element, turn on the (a)toms and check the pulsar settings.. on the interval the atoms will go from being almost invisible to standing front and center. Sometimes, you may need to look hard depending on the various atoms. 

* 's' - save an image of the current state 
* 'a' - activate atoms

The piece is to be experienced by default at 1000x1000, however, have fun with the image. It will adapt to various sizes and create different images by whatever size you view it in. 

@generatecoll 2021

metadata.name: Quantum Vacuum #253
metadata.description:
Empty space is not empty. It's filled with energy, transient fluctuations in quantum fields, bubbling with virtual particles popping in and out of existence. 

Part of an ongoing series of work combining my fascination with the fringes of fundamental physics, the emergence of complex behaviour through the interaction of very simple rules, and my obsession with hacking our perceptual systems. 

/Disclaimer: This is not a simulation, but an artistic conceptual interpretation and dramatization. :)

metadata.name: Visa to the stars #146
metadata.description:
Generative space scenes with an illustrative look.

Use the capture functions to export in big after opening it in its own window, the artwork is full of details.

Press SPACE to show/hide the menu

Control the camera and explore the scene with :
- Mouse Left : Rotate
- Mouse Right : Pan
- Mouse Middle : Zoom

I wrote an article about the project, with a technical breakdown of the piece at https://ulucode.com/wp/visa-to-the-stars/


Decent GPU REQUIRED, you can tune the performances with the "Quality" setting in the menu.
Better performances with Chrome.

Keyboard shortcuts:
SPACE : show/hide menu
A : toggle anti-aliasing
C : take a capture of the ccurrently selected resolution
R : reset camera position/orientation
S : display stats
P : pause animation

metadata.name: Zometric #11
metadata.description:
A journey into geometric shapes.
Real art is not hidden behind complicated and obscure forms. In this collection, we have tried to achieve a unique visual clarity by using the basic visual elements. A pure mixture between piet mondrian and paul klee. A combination of visual language of classical and modern art movements. Over 15 000 combination can be generated.
Made in p5.js
